Curl & Self lovin’ ✨💖✨
.
I was asked the other day, “Why is it that people are drawn to you?” & I answered, “Because I lead with love..”✨
.
As we enter a beautiful new month that is dedicated to LOVE, I want to take a second to send you all a little extra bit of it✨ I have been reflecting a lot on this time, seeing as that I am the only single woman in my group of my friends & it is also the first time that I am single for the big VDAY💖 & at first I was freaking out about it, like I had to prove something to the world in this particular month that I NEEDED love from someone else in order to feel worthy….Until I was reminded just how powerful my ✨OWN LOVE✨is to myself & the love that I have for others as well…Love is my superpower, it is what fuels me, it is what pushes me through the hard times…it is what makes me feel unstoppable✨ 
.
✨This month I challenge you to be a little extra kinder to yourself…tell yourself ONE wonderful thing out loud every day…congratulate yourself on something every day no matter how big or small…do something once a day that makes you smile…& just allow your heart to flourish in the beauty that is YOU✨

There is something so special about being surrounded by so much love, support, strength, inspiration, determination, & most importantly contagious energy✨💖✨ I remember taking a class from @lovebrinnnicole before pandemic happened, at Millennium, and we were in studio B and I remember just looking around and thinking “HOLY SHIZZZ THIS IS A LOT OF PEOPLE!” 😂 but then as we all started learning, I felt a sense of comfort…a sense of home…the feeling that I got all the time when I would train back in NYC & immediately just went straight into TRAINING mode✨ It was one of my first classes that I stood in the back & learned from the people in front of me because obviously I couldn’t see lol! But because her dancers were KILLLLINGGGG it! The strength they exuded, the decisions they made, the musicality/ability to physically see the music slow down as they moved through each movement with grace, poise, & such light!✨
.
Fast forward post pandemic, my first class back with her was when the beautiful Goddess Emma taught with her and I hadn’t been in a class consistently in AWHILE! I was 10lbs heavier, insecure, to be honest, scared…until the moment of gratitude came…Brinn is teaching me so much to be in the moment and enjoying EVERY aspect of each moment down to the littlest pinky toe/finger ✨ I feel such joy whenever I step into her room and I am able to carry it with me every day! She has taught me how to fall in love with dance in a whole new way & most importantly myself✨ Thank you Brinn & to the entire @pumpfidence community for allowing me to be the best possible version of me each & every single time I step out onto that floor!✨💖✨

✨What is Sultry Sunday?✨
✨It’s an evening of dance that empowers, encourages & explores the divine light that is within all of us✨ It is an evening of connection to self both physically & mentally✨ It is a challenge that pushes us to stay in the present moment and to try something new✨ It is an opportunity to express yourself the way YOU want and interpret the movement with the music as to how you feel it✨ It is a moment to indulge in the power that you have and allowing it to come to the forefront✨ It is YOUR time to shine, your time to discover, & your time to be the most authentic version of who you are✨

✨ OPEN level class which means that ALL levels of dance are welcome from beginner to professionals✨ We explore technique, posture, engagement, performance, and break everything down so that all levels are receiving the push that they need/want.✨ It is an encouraging community of people that welcomes any & everyone from all walks of life (18+)✨ POP-UP style classes….for now 😈✨

There is something so unapologetically beautiful about the notion of unplugging. Not just from technology, but also from the energy, the thoughts, the constant day to day expectations…all things that I know we ALL feel on a daily basis. 

And while yes, we do hold ourselves to such expectations, thoughts, & energies we still need to find time for us…time to allow ourselves to know the difference between resting vs Quitting. 

The harsh reality is that, yes it is never going to be easy…anything that we decide to do, anytime we challenge ourselves, anytime we hold ourselves accountable and strive for the greatness that is in ALL of us…the road is long and it can be taxing. But the even harsher reality, in my opinion, is working so hard that you let your life go by without acknowledging the moments that helped to shape that greatness…the smaller moments of acknowledgment, of thought, of re-meeting your inner child & allowing them to play, laugh, & just feeling free. 

These are the detailed moments, in my opinion, that help you get clear about what you really want & how to go about doing it. The moments where you are so open to receiving the blessings that are already written for you…without cloudiness, without expectation, & without a second thought that you are not worthy.

✨Reset, Recharge, Refuel….and then go out and be the greatest you✨However that may look for you✨
